When igniting a new app, if the user chooses to install dependencies we run the following:

```
   // #region Install CocoaPods
    // install pods
    if (shouldFreshInstallDeps) {
      startSpinner("Baking CocoaPods")
      await spawnProgress(`npx pod-install@${deps.podInstall}`, {
        onProgress: log,
      })
      stopSpinner("Baking CocoaPods", "☕️")
    }
    // #endregion
```

Is it possible this action is then duplicated via our `./boilerplate/bin/postInstall` script during `yarn install`? This script also goes through the necessary MacOS and ios folder checks to then run `pod install`.

